======================================================================
ANALYSIS 6: Rank-nullity tracking
======================================================================
For d_2: Om_2 -> Om_1: rk + nullity = dim(Om_2)
nullity = dim(Z_2) = dim(Om_2) - rk(d_2)
d_3: Om_3 -> Om_2: rk + nullity = dim(Om_3)
beta_2 = dim(Z_2) - rk(d_3)

We need: delta(beta_2) = 0
  <=> delta(dim Z_2) = delta(rk d_3)
  <=> delta(dim Om_2) - delta(rk d_2) = delta(rk d_3)
  <=> delta(dim Om_2) + delta(beta_1) = delta(rk d_3)  [since drk2=-db1]

Let's track delta(rk d_3) vs delta(dim Om_3) - delta(nullity d_3)
(dOm2, dOm3, drk2, drk3, db1) distribution:
  dOm2=-1, dOm3=-6, drk2=+1, drk3=-2, db1=-1 | dZ2=-2, dZ3=-4 | OK | count=120
