======================================================================
ANALYSIS 7: Can we express drk3 as dOm3 - dZ3?
======================================================================
Since drk3 = dOm2 + db1 (our target identity),
this means dOm3 - dZ3 = dOm2 + db1
=> dZ3 = dOm3 - dOm2 - db1
=> delta(dim Z_3) = delta(dim Om_3) - delta(dim Om_2) - delta(beta_1)

  Verification errors: 0
  CONFIRMED: delta(Z_3) = delta(Om_3) - delta(Om_2) - delta(beta_1)
  This is EQUIVALENT to beta_2=0 invariance, not an independent fact.

